a good reason for this?

02:51.472 --> 02:53.972
(with french accent)
i am an international superstar.

02:53.974 --> 02:57.142
I will not be handcuffed
to a radiator.

02:57.144 --> 03:00.512
Hey, you said that just like
anastasia boulangerie

03:00.514 --> 03:04.416
In the blockbuster thriller
<i>i will not be 'andcuffed</i>
<i>to a radiator.</i>

03:05.519 --> 03:07.052
-Riley?
-Yeah?

03:07.054 --> 03:09.288
That is anastasia boulangerie.

03:12.493 --> 03:17.262
Yeeeeeeeeeeee!

03:18.499 --> 03:20.132
Where are my cookies?

03:20.134 --> 03:22.334
-What?
-I want my french cookies.

03:22.336 --> 03:23.969
Do you know
what they are called?

03:23.971 --> 03:25.170
Macaroons!

03:25.172 --> 03:29.041
Yes! You will be
my new cookie bringer!

03:29.043 --> 03:31.510
Yay! Maya, yay!

03:31.512 --> 03:34.580
Riley, focus. We kidnapped
anastasia boulangerie.

03:34.582 --> 03:38.150
Oh! Well, go big or go home,
i always say.

03:41.055 --> 03:43.755
Really?
Never lost a case, huh?

03:43.757 --> 03:45.157
-Think you ever will?
-No.

03:45.159 --> 03:46.391
Ha-ha!

03:50.898 --> 03:54.266
This is not crème fraîche.
This is whipped cream.

03:54.268 --> 03:55.601
From a store.

03:56.937 --> 04:00.038
I have failed you.

04:00.040 --> 04:04.443
Oh, and you, street rat.
You call this a flower?

04:04.445 --> 04:07.446
No, no, no.
I call this a blob.

04:07.448 --> 04:11.083
-Look, lady, you're
not our guest, you're being--
-borrowed.

04:11.085 --> 04:12.884
-What?
-Borrowed is what we did.

04:12.886 --> 04:15.187
I don't like the other word.
I like borrowed.

04:15.189 --> 04:16.588
I-- i don't think
it makes a difference.

04:16.590 --> 04:18.023
Oh, yes, i think it does.

04:18.025 --> 04:19.858
I don't mind being borrowed.

04:19.860 --> 04:23.061
It's romantic,
like a fountain.

04:23.063 --> 04:24.930
Get me a fountain.

04:25.899 --> 04:27.532
(laughing)

04:27.534 --> 04:30.535
Why, you're laughing
because where are we gonna get
a fountain?

04:30.537 --> 04:32.871
No, i'm laughing
because what on earth
is my father going

04:32.873 --> 04:34.640
To put on the board
for this one?

04:38.078 --> 04:39.511
Squeak!

04:47.054 --> 04:49.821
I wanted a chocolate fountain.

04:54.428 --> 04:57.629
And i wanted a chance
for my mom to play
one great role.

04:58.565 --> 05:01.667
You went too far,
do you understand?

05:01.669 --> 05:03.435
And i went too far
because i am your best friend,

05:03.437 --> 05:05.837
But there are limits
to best friendship.

05:05.839 --> 05:08.073
There are no limits to us.

05:08.075 --> 05:11.510
Good! Now, let's
just not do anything
that could get us caught.

05:15.849 --> 05:18.250
(shutter clicking)

05:19.753 --> 05:22.921
Look, i know what we did
was wrong, but the reason
i did it

05:22.923 --> 05:24.990
Is because my mom's up
for a movie, and i think
she could really

05:24.992 --> 05:26.692
-Be right for the role.
-What is it?

05:26.694 --> 05:28.694
The role of katy,
a down-on-her-luck waitress

05:28.696 --> 05:31.029
Who's always wanted
to be an actress,
has one daughter

05:31.031 --> 05:32.431
And one last shot at love.

05:32.433 --> 05:35.300
There is only one person
in the world who could play
this role!

05:35.302 --> 05:37.436
-I know.
-Anastasia boulangerie!

05:37.438 --> 05:39.371
Yes, of course
i will play the role!

05:39.373 --> 05:40.605
I am perfect
for everything!

05:40.607 --> 05:44.976
Wait. Why did maya
borrow you if you already
have the role?

05:44.978 --> 05:48.980
Are you not telling me
the whole truth,
anastasia boulangerie?

05:48.982 --> 05:54.386
Okay. Okay, there may be
a certain insignificant
unknown who is

05:54.388 --> 05:57.689
Also up for the role.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.524
And it's katy hunter,
isn't it?

05:59.526 --> 06:03.395
Yes. Katy 'unter.

06:03.397 --> 06:06.231
Well, why don't you
just let maya's mother
have this one,

06:06.233 --> 06:10.135
And you go play
queen francy-pants of france?

06:10.137 --> 06:11.803
Are we leakin' again?

06:11.805 --> 06:13.638
Oh, we got a fountain.

06:15.509 --> 06:16.742
Bobbie jo?

06:16.744 --> 06:19.878
I am sure i have no idea
of this bobbie jo who you say.

06:19.880 --> 06:24.149
Oh, knock off
the phony accent, bobbie jo,
i know who you are.

06:24.151 --> 06:30.021
(hillbilly accent)
okay, fine! But this here
does not leave this here room!

06:30.023 --> 06:32.524
-What?
-The?

06:32.526 --> 06:36.428
I always promised
to keep your secret
and i always have.

06:36.430 --> 06:37.662
Yeah, katy, you always have.

06:37.664 --> 06:40.732
Mom, you know her?

06:40.734 --> 06:45.404
Oh! We kind of
grew up together.

06:45.406 --> 06:48.673
You grew up
with queen pantsy-france
of pants?

06:48.675 --> 06:51.076
Maya, i'm sorry
i never told you
about bobbie jo,

06:51.078 --> 06:52.577
But she made me promise.

06:52.579 --> 06:54.579
Well, if this got out,
it could ruin everything
for me!

06:54.581 --> 06:56.148
What is it?

06:58.385 --> 07:00.886
Anastasia boulangerie
is not from france.

07:00.888 --> 07:02.254
Both:
What?

07:02.256 --> 07:03.822
See?

07:04.758 --> 07:06.091
Where is she from?

07:06.093 --> 07:09.528
She is from possum trot,
arkansas.

07:09.530 --> 07:12.030
-Both: What?
-See?

07:12.032 --> 07:13.598
But you're from
possum trot, arkansas.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.801
-What?
-Riley, you knew that.

07:15.803 --> 07:17.636
I can't stop.

07:17.638 --> 07:20.639
Maya, you know how
maya hart has riley matthews.

07:20.641 --> 07:21.940
Always and forever.

07:21.942 --> 07:26.778
Well, katy grace clutterbucket
always thought she'd have...

07:26.780 --> 07:30.982
-Bobbie jo thibodeaux.
-How do?

07:30.984 --> 07:34.052
Your best friend
was anastasia boulangerie?

07:34.054 --> 07:37.923
No. Uh, my best friend
was bobbie jo thibodeaux.

07:37.925 --> 07:41.560
I was never very close
to anastasia boulangerie,
who left.

07:41.562 --> 07:47.065
But at one time,
we would've done anything
for each other.

07:47.067 --> 07:49.868
Maya, i don't understand.
How could this happen
to best friends?

07:52.773 --> 07:55.006
Well, mom, do you want me
to set her free?

07:56.777 --> 07:59.044
No, mama really
wants this role.

08:01.748 --> 08:04.783
No, really,
how good a lawyer
are you?

08:04.785 --> 08:06.785
Ha-ha.

08:06.787 --> 08:07.819
Ha-ha.

08:12.993 --> 08:17.796
So, we all heard
from yogi's father,
officer yogi,

08:17.798 --> 08:19.364
About gritty real life.

08:19.366 --> 08:22.601
And now, to talk to you guys
about a life of imagination,

08:22.603 --> 08:25.704
Is sarah's father,
a movie director.

08:25.706 --> 08:28.039
The policeman had nothing
to do with us.

08:28.041 --> 08:30.075
(whispers)
we're in the clear.

08:31.712 --> 08:36.681
I'm... A movie director.

08:36.683 --> 08:38.183
We're fine.

08:38.185 --> 08:44.523
And my next project is
the new anastasia boulangerie,
yeah, movie.

08:47.194 --> 08:49.861
We're less fine.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.062
Does anybody know
where she is?

08:51.064 --> 08:54.566
-Go crazy.
-Bark!

08:54.568 --> 08:57.969
My name is dw preminger,
and i have my wonderful daughter
to thank for the idea

08:57.971 --> 09:01.039
Behind my new film
about a struggling waitress.

09:01.041 --> 09:02.807
-And her daughter
-and her friends!

09:02.809 --> 09:05.911
Yeah, that's right.
You think i've just
been sitting here?

09:05.913 --> 09:07.913
I've been taking notes!

09:07.915 --> 09:09.581
I've been writing
my screenplay.

09:11.385 --> 09:14.185
But in the fairy tale town
that is hollywood,

09:14.187 --> 09:18.890
There is actually
an upstart contender
challenging ms. Boulangerie

09:18.892 --> 09:21.493
For this role,
and you know,
it just might happen,

09:21.495 --> 09:26.231
Because the world loves
an undiscovered underdog.

09:26.233 --> 09:29.100
And also because...
We can't find the other one.

09:29.102 --> 09:31.903
So, does anybody
know where she is?

09:31.905 --> 09:33.271
Both:
No!

09:33.273 --> 09:36.708
I believe there was
another thing you
wanted to tell them, dw?

09:36.710 --> 09:39.744
You know what else
the audience likes?

09:39.746 --> 09:42.380
"authenticity!"

09:42.382 --> 09:46.952
So, in the interest
of authenticity,
dw preminger's going

09:46.954 --> 09:51.590
To extend an invitation
to the real life friends
of his daughter's imagination

09:51.592 --> 09:57.028
Because what could be
more hollywood authentic
than holding out false hope...

09:58.865 --> 10:03.902
To you, who inspired the roles,
to audition for the roles,
of dookas...

10:03.904 --> 10:05.136
-Dookas?
-Zed--

10:05.138 --> 10:08.139
-Zed?
