call this a kidnapping.

14:42.048 --> 14:46.851
Okay, fine, it wasn't.
I knew it was maya
from all the pictures

14:46.853 --> 14:48.586
I'd seen of you.

14:48.588 --> 14:49.721
You looked me up?

14:49.723 --> 14:51.089
Maybe a little.

14:51.091 --> 14:52.690
You checkin' up on us?

14:52.692 --> 14:54.492
Congratulations
on gettin' married again.

14:54.494 --> 14:56.060
He seems like
a really a good man.

14:56.062 --> 14:58.263
He's wonderful.

14:58.265 --> 15:01.900
I got my baby girl
and a husband
who loves me.

15:01.902 --> 15:04.235
I love my life.

15:04.237 --> 15:08.606
Yeah. I love my life, too.

15:08.608 --> 15:14.012
So... (clears throat)
you will not be auditioning
for the role of katy anymore?

15:14.014 --> 15:17.982
Against you?
Me against you
for the role of me?

15:19.552 --> 15:23.121
Oh...
No, i'll be auditioning.

15:25.258 --> 15:27.191
And i'm gonna beat you.

15:29.195 --> 15:31.262
They were best friends
once, maya.

15:31.264 --> 15:34.098
-Now they're
going against each other.
-Best friends are supposed

15:34.100 --> 15:36.935
To stay best friends.
-Mm, i don't think
they know that.

15:46.613 --> 15:48.613
Hey, sarah.

15:48.615 --> 15:52.917
We're here to audition
for the roles of dookas,
zed and farkle.

15:52.919 --> 15:55.219
Yeah, you and the rest
of the city.

16:02.262 --> 16:04.062
I'm not happy!

16:04.064 --> 16:06.431
I'm wearin' my cowboy hat.

16:06.433 --> 16:09.167
I'm wearin'
my cowboy hat!

16:09.169 --> 16:12.170
My moment's gonna be
my cowboy hat!

16:12.172 --> 16:13.938
Am i an idiot?

16:13.940 --> 16:17.508
I withhold judgment
because i'm smart enough
to know what happens next.

16:17.510 --> 16:20.111
Lucas! I'm up in the air!

16:20.113 --> 16:23.147
Yeah, that's how i did it.

16:23.149 --> 16:25.116
Anastasia! There you are,
my darling!

16:25.118 --> 16:26.584
Where have you been?

16:26.586 --> 16:29.320
(french accent) i took
some time to consider
my, how you say, priorities.

16:29.322 --> 16:30.588
-What?
-Priorities.

16:30.590 --> 16:32.323
-What?
-(hillbilly accent)
i been thinkin' about stuff!

16:32.325 --> 16:33.491
What just happened?

16:34.961 --> 16:36.861
All right, look...

16:36.863 --> 16:42.166
I'm all for hollywood
fairy tales...
But the truth is,

16:42.168 --> 16:45.269
She's a big box office draw,
and you're not.

16:45.271 --> 16:46.838
Anastasia,
the role is yours,
unless someone

16:46.840 --> 16:48.206
Has a real good reason
why it isn't.

16:48.208 --> 16:50.375
-Authenticity?
-Sorry. What?

16:50.377 --> 16:52.477
You said that authenticity
was a very big deal to you?

16:52.479 --> 16:55.213
No, i said that authenticity
was a very big deal
to the audience.

16:55.215 --> 16:57.348
I prefer pretty people
sayin' stuff.

16:57.350 --> 17:01.219
My mother's pretty,
and she says stuff
just as good as she does.

17:01.221 --> 17:04.856
Yeah?
Let's see if that's so.

17:04.858 --> 17:06.824
Would you
like a moment to prepare?

17:06.826 --> 17:08.493
I've been prepared
my whole life.

17:08.495 --> 17:09.527
I know it by heart.

17:09.529 --> 17:12.296
I'll read the parts
of smiley and banana.

17:12.298 --> 17:14.866
-Banana?
-I'm smiley!

17:14.868 --> 17:20.538
No, i'm going
to perform the scene
to this riley and this maya.

17:20.540 --> 17:22.440
Because they've always
kept me real.

17:26.346 --> 17:30.381
Actually,
it only looks like
nothin' ever went right for me.

17:32.252 --> 17:34.085
Maybe bein' walked out on
by the wrong guy

17:34.087 --> 17:36.220
Is what allowed
the right guy to walk in.

17:38.425 --> 17:43.828
Maybe watchin' my daughter
discover the joy
of a best friend

17:43.830 --> 17:48.666
Is what teaches me
who mine really are.

17:48.668 --> 17:51.302
And maybe bein' apart...

17:53.440 --> 17:58.676
Is supposed to show you
how hard you're supposed
to fight to stay together.

17:58.678 --> 18:02.580
'cause a true friend
is the best thing
that life has to offer.

18:05.051 --> 18:06.350
Anastasia?

18:06.352 --> 18:08.019
I could never beat that.

18:08.021 --> 18:10.922
-Why not?
-Because i, uh...
(clears throat)

18:10.924 --> 18:12.056
Don't believe in it.

18:12.058 --> 18:14.592
Yes, maybe i'm this,
so i could be that,
pish-posh.

18:14.594 --> 18:17.562
I am who i am,
and this is who i am.

18:17.564 --> 18:21.499
Give the role to her.
She was born to play it.

18:22.735 --> 18:25.403
But you're
anastasia boulangerie.

18:25.405 --> 18:27.472
And she is katy hunter.

18:27.474 --> 18:29.140
Real person.

18:29.142 --> 18:30.475
Bravo.

18:35.615 --> 18:37.949
Be careful bein' famous.

18:37.951 --> 18:39.650
It's easy to forget
who you are.

18:41.588 --> 18:44.789
Girls! You
can borrow me anytime!

18:47.093 --> 18:48.960
<i>Au revoir!</i>

18:51.064 --> 18:55.066
-♪ i'm bobbie jo ♪
-♪ i'm katy grace ♪

19:00.240 --> 19:02.573
-I want to play smiley!
-You're not right for it.

19:02.575 --> 19:04.575
Okay!

19:09.349 --> 19:13.618
Mr. Matthews,
what do you call
being best friends with someone

19:13.620 --> 19:17.088
One day and then
growing apart forever?

19:17.090 --> 19:19.090
Unfortunately,
i call that normal, maya.

19:19.092 --> 19:20.992
No.

19:20.994 --> 19:23.494
Don't worry, maya.
Nothing could change us.

19:23.496 --> 19:25.229
Not even hollywood.

19:26.799 --> 19:28.065
Huh!

19:36.543 --> 19:39.911
Thank you!
Thank you very much!

19:41.314 --> 19:43.781
Oh, my gosh!
Farkle, you got the part!

19:43.783 --> 19:46.150
No.

19:46.152 --> 19:47.785
Just keepin' the costume?

19:47.787 --> 19:50.454
What costume?

19:50.456 --> 19:52.557
Yeah, listen up, sy.
You tell them

19:52.559 --> 19:56.394
I only want to be semi-regular.
All right?

19:56.396 --> 19:59.230
I show up when i want to,
tell 'em to get workin'
on my catch phrases.

19:59.232 --> 20:04.135
I don't know,
somethin' like...
Zay what?

20:04.137 --> 20:05.670
Zay, you got the part!

20:05.672 --> 20:07.371
No.

20:13.012 --> 20:16.414
-Um, lucas?
-I'm not lucas anymore.

20:16.416 --> 20:20.384
I'm taylor tristan cool cool
poopy pants mcstupidhead.

20:22.355 --> 20:23.554
You got the part!

20:23.556 --> 20:25.790
Yup.

20:27.594 --> 20:28.826
Really?

20:28.828 --> 20:30.161
No!

20:33.833 --> 20:36.734
Well... Maya?

20:38.371 --> 20:40.371
I've decided
that when i grow up...

20:40.373 --> 20:44.208
I want
to be my mother's daughter,

20:44.210 --> 20:48.379
I want to be riley's friend,
and i want us all to know

20:48.381 --> 20:49.513
How important we are
to each other.

20:50.516 --> 20:52.350
I would do anything
for you.

20:52.352 --> 20:53.751
I know.

21:01.227 --> 21:03.694
Farkle reading for the role
of farkle.

21:03.696 --> 21:04.895
Any questions?

21:04.897 --> 21:06.430
Yeah, how do you--
how do you want this guy?

21:06.432 --> 21:08.266
Farkly.

21:08.268 --> 21:10.534
There was the very fast-talking
farkle where everybody
would yell at me--

21:10.536 --> 21:12.536
-Slow down!
-Yeah, like that.

21:12.538 --> 21:14.305
And then there was
donnie barnes, regular guy!

21:14.307 --> 21:15.873
I'd see that movie.

21:15.875 --> 21:17.475
And now
there's the current farkle,
who's somewhere

21:17.477 --> 21:19.710
Between nerd-chic
and teenage heartthrob
poster boy.

21:22.081 --> 21:24.448
Next!

21:24.450 --> 21:25.483
Yeah, okay.

21:27.787 --> 21:30.821
Hello. Lucas friar,
auditioning for the role
of dookas.

21:30.823 --> 21:35.593
-Okay... Dookas
is the strong, silent type.
-Okay.

21:35.595 --> 21:40.631
He's able to convey
a lot of emotions
through very few words.

21:40.633 --> 21:42.600
Okay.

21:42.602 --> 21:44.268
He's got a smoldering presence

21:44.270 --> 21:47.571
That makes men want to be him,

21:47.573 --> 21:50.408
And women want
to be with him.

21:50.410 --> 21:54.512
Okay.

21:54.514 --> 21:56.013
Do you do accents?

21:58.351 --> 22:02.119
I am mortimer
twigglebottom smythe!

22:02.121 --> 22:03.321
Next!

22:11.931 --> 22:14.165
(exhaling)

22:15.435 --> 22:19.270
She ate... My cookie, man!

22:19.272 --> 22:20.604
Next!

22:20.606 --> 22:23.307
Zay what?

22:23.309 --> 22:25.509
Hold on, do that again.

22:25.511 --> 22:28.646
Zay what?

22:28.648 --> 22:30.581
Now, next.
